postcontent: I have for sale a very nice Swedish Mauser Model M38 made in 1941 by the Husqvarna factory. They were the only factory to build purpose built M38's, the rest of them were modified from M96 rifles and are not as desirable as this one. This one is in very good condition with all matching numbers except for the cleaning rod.  The rifle has a stock disk.  The bore is bright and shiny with good rifling.  This rifle is chambered in the Swedish 6.5 x 55 cartridge, which has relatively low recoil, but still packs a punch.  These rifles make excellent hunting guns, and are known for their outstanding accuracy.  The rifle includes an original sling and the cleaning rod.More photos are available upon request.  I can be reached through the Armslist site, or by text at REDACTED.

postcontent: This is the oldest model of a Smith & Wesson Chiefs Special that I have owned. It is a pre-Model 36 version J-frame built in 1956. That's right...this classic snubnose revolver is sixty years old but you couldn't tell it by looking at or shooting it. Designed to be small and compact for easy carry conceal or small storage areas, this pre-Model 36 Flat Latch J-frame Chiefs Special has a pinned 1.875 inch (sometimes called a 2 inch) barrel. It has 5-round capacity in a swing-out cylinder and can be fired in single or double action. This gun has a grooved rear sight and a ramped fixed blade front sight. It features a blued finish and has the original diamond-type wood grips with serial numbers that match the round butt frame.This classic S&W revolver is in great condition for its age. There is some honest holster wear on the bottom front of the frame and muzzle and a small chip in the bottom of the upper portion of the right wood grip. This gun was carried some but only occasionally fired. Very clean and shiny bore and cylinders with no rust or damage on this gun. I had the gun's side plate off and completely cleaned while intact the internals, then oiled them before replacing the side plate. That helped improve an already smooth trigger and added to the accuracy of the gun.I have fired 50 problem-free rounds of factory .38 Special 130 grain factory ammunition through it since I acquired it. As with all of the S&W revolvers I have had the pleasure to shoot, this one is fun and confidence-inspiring. This revolver is one that is of the age it could be put away in a collection to fondle and admire, but is also dependable and accurate enough to carry conceal or use as a house gun.
